==English==
===Etymology===
From the Greek ''kalliope'', from ''kalli-'', (beauty) + ''opos'', (voice).

===Noun===

'''calliope'''

# A musical instrument, consistong of steam whistles played with a keyboard organ. 

===Proper noun===

'''Calliope'''

# (''Greek mythology''): The [[Muse]] of [[eloquence]] and [[epic]] or heroic poetry; mother of [[Orpheus]] with [[Apollo]].
